Fidelity International Gets Nod to Sell Investment Products in China
Fidelity International is the first major foreign fund manager to get such a permission

 






By

Rachel Rosenthal


Rachel Rosenthal
The Wall Street Journal
BiographyRachel Rosenthal
@rosenthalrc
rachel.rosenthal@wsj.com




  Updated Jan. 4, 2017 6:52 a.m. ET





Chinese financial regulators have given Fidelity International the green light to offer local investment products to wealthy mainland investors, making it the first major foreign fund manager to get such a permission. The company’s Chinese operation, FIL Investment Management (Shanghai) Co., has this week registered with the Asset Management Association of China as a private fund-management company. That step allows the firm to...
  


