Company structure  About FidelityCareersRemunerationMediaHomeCompany structureFIL Limited (FIL) provides investment products and services to individuals, institutions and multi-national corporations and their advisers.
Our product range spans:

Mutual funds
Defined contribution pensions
Segregated portfolios
MultiManager

We have online investment platforms in the UK, Germany and Taiwan (FundsNetwork™).
Company structure and history
FIL is a privately owned investment management company incorporated in 1969 and is the ultimate holding company of an international group of companies (FIL and its consolidated subsidiaries, together "Fidelity").
In 1969, a Tokyo office was opened. It was the first foreign (non-Japanese) asset management company to open in Japan. In 1973, our first European base was established in London.
FIL Limited today operates in Asia Pacific, Europe and the Middle East. It has an extensive network of offices in 24 countries and employs more than 5,000 people.
It manages assets in 11 locations: London, Bermuda, Milan, Frankfurt, Paris, Tokyo, Hong Kong, Mumbai, Seoul, Singapore and Sydney. The Company operates fund platforms in the UK, Germany and Taiwan.Other Fidelity sites:  Fidelity careers  Show site indexAbout usMediaLegal InformationAbout FidelityCareersRemunerationMedia© FIL Limited
							
								
 


